OL,6,F"No single organisation is to blame,
OL,7,Fand everybody is working on making it
OL,8,Fbetter, especially for young people,
OL,9,Fwho are growing up in a world
OL,10,Fdifferent to Mark Zuckerberg or to the
OL,11,Fregulators as well, where it's just
OL,12,Fnormal to be on a screen as often as
OL,13,Fyou can be, and that brings with it
OL,14,Fhealth risks and it brings
OL,15,Fopportunities too.
OL,17,F"I think balancing those things out is
